message.content:
A custard apple is a tropical fruit that grows on the custard apple tree.
It is also known as a sugar apple, due to its sweet flavor.
The fruit is typically green and bumpy on the outside, with a rough, scaly texture.
When ripe, it may have slightly yellow or brownish spots and a softer texture.
Inside, it contains creamy white flesh and numerous black seeds.
Custard apples are commonly found in warm regions such as South America, India, and Southeast Asia.
In addition to being eaten fresh, the fruit is also used in desserts and drinks.
